hypothesis `mpb` states that `|nth_partial i f x| ≤ M` for some `M`. We can use this to bound the mixed partial derivatives.\n\nLet's continue with the proof structure:\n\n```tactics\n  have h5 : |g'' 0| ≤ C * ε^2 := by\n    simp [g'']\n    have h6 : ∀ i j, |(nth_partial i <| nth_partial j f) x| ≤ C := by\n      intro i j\n      have h7 : |(nth_partial i <| nth_partial j f) x| ≤ |nth_partial i f x| * |nth_partial j f x| := by\n        simp [abs_mul]\n      have h8 : |nth_partial i f x| ≤ M := by\n        apply abs_le_of_nonneg\n        · -- Show that |nth_partial i f x| ≤ M\n          sorry\n        · -- Show that 0 ≤ M\n          sorry\n      have h9 : |nth_partial j f x| ≤ M := by\n        apply abs_le_of_nonneg\n        · -- Show that |nth_partial j f x| ≤ M\n          sorry\n        · -- Show that 0 ≤ M\n          sorry\n      nlinarith\n    have h7 : ∑ i, ∑ j, (y i - x i) * (y j - x j) * |(nth_partial i <| nth_partial j f) x| ≤ ∑ i, ∑ j, (y i - x i) * (y j - x j) * M := by\n      apply Finset.sum_le_sum\n      intro i hi\n      apply Finset.sum_le_sum\n      intro j hj\n      have h8 : |(y i - x i) * (y j - x j)| ≤ 1 := by\n        have h9 : |y i - x i| ≤ ε := by\n          apply hdiff i\n        have h10 : |y j - x j| ≤ ε := by\n          apply hdiff j\n        have h11 : |(y i - x i) * (y j - x j)| ≤ ε * ε := by\n          apply abs_mul\n          all_goals linarith [h9, h10]\n        nlinarith [sq_nonneg (ε), hε]\n      have h9 : |(nth_partial i <| nth_partial j f) x| ≤ M := h6 i j\n      nlinarith\n    sorry\n```\n\nThe proof of `h5` is also incomplete. We need to use `mpb` more directly. The hypothesis `mpb` gives us a bound on `|nth_partial i f x|`. We need to relate this to the mixed partial derivatives.\n\nLet's assume we have `h4` and `h5` proven. We can now complete the proof:\n\n```tactics\n  rw [h2]\n  have h6 : |f x - f y| = |(g 1 - g 0)| := by\n    rw [h2]\n    all_goals simp [abs_neg]\n  rw [h6]\n  have h7 : |g 1 - g 0| ≤ ε * ∑ i, |nth_partial i 