`L_f(g(t)) (y - x) = ∑ i, (f i)'(g(t)) * (y i - x i)`.
So the derivative of `f ∘ g` at `t` is `∑ i, (f i)'(g(t)) * (y i - x i)`.
This is exactly what we want.

